      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THEROUX (7) is in a purple patch of form with wins at his last three starts, most recently when he made a sustained run from the back half of the field and was too good by 6.7m at this circuit ad distance. Interesting to see what unfolds from this wide draw but winning form is hard to knock. CLIVES GIRL (2) came from wider when she won at this venue two starts ago before racing wide in the latter stages and finishing third at her latest appearance at Shepparton. Should enjoy an economical run from this draw so could get the job done. SHEZABLUECHIP (1) drew wide and worked at Charlton on Monday but won from the back row at Shepparton prior. Aided by the ace draw so worth another chance. ALABAMA ICE (8) has won when second-up before so is a player after his last-start fourth when resuming at Shepparton.",
